# Intake — bowling-shirt-designer

Parsed Upwork posting + orchestrator decisions into `brief.json`.

## Key assignments from brief

**Client problem:** E-commerce apparel customizer broken by dead clicks (`undefined is not an object`) + homepage bounce from script blocking. Needs audit + Remediation Roadmap.

**Michael's demo:** Full-featured bowling shirt store with 3D interactive customizer (pattern library, color picker, text-on-back), product page + cart, audit credibility section. Proves architectural rigor + performance optimization that directly solves client's exact problems.

**Architecture:**
- Frontend: Vite + React 18 + Three.js + @react-three/fiber (avoids Redux boilerplate bugs; Zustand for state)
- Backend: Flask blueprint on mw-backend (POST/GET /bowling/patterns, /bowling/customize, /bowling/sessions)
- Deployment: Vite build → `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/bowling-shirt-designer/` (static, same-origin)
- Design: Retro-modern bowling alley (navy #1a1f3c, cream #f5f0e8, coral #e84040, gold #f5a623)

**Feature scope (richness 10/10):**
1. Hero: 3D customizer (orbit controls, 6+ patterns + upload, live textures, color pickers, text-on-back)
2. Supporting 1: Product page + cart (size selector, localStorage persistence, thumbnail preview)
3. Supporting 2: Audit credibility section (error pattern vs. architectural solutions)

**Hard gates:**
- Visible 3D shirt with applied texture (blank canvas = fail)
- Pattern upload works live (user picks file, shirt updates instantly)
- Text-on-back visible on 3D model (not just form field)
- Cart shows customization thumbnail
- Zero console errors on first paint
- Fast homepage load (deferred Three.js canvas proves optimization)
- Cover letter names Microsoft Clarity + dead-click diagnosis

**Critical path:** Researcher MUST find free bowling/short-sleeve shirt GLTF model before demo-builder starts. Fallback: procedural plane-based shirt. UV texture mapping for text-on-back may need custom model or canvas-overlay approach.

## handoff
- produced: `brief.json` — full structured intake (posting summary, Michael's vision, architecture decisions, 3-feature list, design tokens, hard gates, risks, scope fence)
- decisions: Vite+React+Three.js static app (no Node server); 3 features all fully working; PHP proxy in proposal narrative only; Flask backend real; retro bowling palette (zero michaelwegter.com tokens)
- next needs: Planner locks detailed feature/design spec + component tree; researcher finds free shirt GLTF + 6+ pattern assets + three.js customizer UX reference; demo-builder executes with zero console errors on first paint
- risks: GLTF availability is blocker (researcher owns); UV layout for text-on-back may require custom approach; Three.js material swaps must render on first paint with patterns applied
